The paper deals with the problem of constructing flow-sparsifiers, which is a topic in network engineering (cs.NE) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and sketching techniques (cs.SI) to compress the network. Finally, the paper presents results on the size of the sparsifiers, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
